Nov 24 2009 	Not awful but a hard place to recommend	I booked a super cheap rate months ago at hotels.com and thought about changing to a better hotel many times as the date of our trip approached. In the end I stuck with my Fitzgeralds reservation with the thought that the money saved would be used for food and games. Now home after 4 nights in LV, I'm having a hard time deciding if I can recommend the Fitz even for the low, low nightly rate. Our room was on a floor that had been remodeled recently. Well, the halls had been remodeled and looked very nice. Seeing that, I was really optimistic about the place until I opened the door to our room. Our guest room had 2 double beds, an armoire, dresser and a nightstand. The &quot;wooden&quot; furniture looked a little like the kind of thing you buy at Target and put together. Not bad, but fairly cheap looking. The beds were on the low end of acceptability. The TV had a decent selection of channels and good picture. The bathtub faucet leaked continuously and looked a little worn. The A/C worked fine but was a little loud. The overall effect of the room was one of advancing age and wear. One of my biggest concerns was the elevators. I had heard of a history of long delays waiting for an elevator and how this was now less of a problem since some of the elevators had been replaced, I'm sorry to say that it is still a problem when the hotel gets busy. Sunday morning I waited 15 minutes for a down elevator before giving up and taking an up elevator and riding back down. That is really unacceptable. I did not eat in the Fitz but ate at the Four Queens and Fremont which are steps away from the Fitz,Everyone I met at the Fitz who talked about the condition of the hotel said something like &quot;well, for the money it's okay.&quot; Personally, if I had it to do over again I'd spend another $10 -15 a night for the Fremont of 4 Queens. For that I'd get a better bed, elevators that worked and in hotel restaurants that I am willing to eat in. The best part of the Fitz was the valet service. It was exceptional and very friendly.	
