Aug 17 2009 	Great Stay No complaints!	First let me apologize for the delay in posting my review. This review was from a trip that i took at the end of may. I've been going to Vegas for the past 4 years, I find that Vegas is still the most affordable place to take vacation. The entire package was just under $800 for three people, including round trip airfare, and 4 nights in the hotel. We stayed at the fitzgeralds, this is my second time staying there. The first trip was with my dad, and we a had wonderful time as well, so good that i booked this trip at the same hotel. The Fitzgeralds is an older hotel, as many of the downtown hotels are. The room quality is good, a little worn around the edges but not dirty. I've read many complaints about the elevators, there are signs posted stating that they are in the process of upgrading their elevators. We personally weren't affected by long wait times, or over crowding of the elevator cars. We stayed on the 17th floor, and never had to wait over 3 minutes for an elevator. The staff we encountered were all very friendly, polite and helpful. The only place we ate at the fitz was the McDonalds located next to the casino. The prices there were the same as home, and they had the dollar menu. We avoided the Fitz buffet because of the poor reviews, the Main Street Station and Fremont have very nice buffets. The room was very adequate for our needs, and served it's purpose well, we were never back to our room before midnight so noise from the Fremont experience wasn't an issue. The view wasn't spectacular, but did look out to the mountains, which was nice. The curtains are the very thick &quot;Black-Out&quot; type which is great when you end up getting in around sun-rise and need to power nap before hitting the town again :-D My overall experience with the Fitzgeralds was great, The only minor thing was the narrow paths in the parking garage, very little room to move if another car was coming, and the winding up to the 6th floor was a little dizzying, but then again it's a small garage, for a small hotel. They do have a pool, however we didn't make use of it, but did see it, it's not in the nicest location. The pool is right next to the rear access road, and is surrounded by 7foot tall concrete walls, looks like a pool cell more than a pool area, and the pool was a simple square shape, but the water was clean and blue so that's a good thing :-)	
