Dec 16 2007	Had a great time at the Fitz December 6 to 13 2007	We enjoyed our stay at the Fitz. When I booked, I asked for a room on a higher floor and away from the Fremont Street Experience. We got room 3236 facing west with a view of the downtown casinos. It was a good-sized room, clean, comfortable with a large bathroom, a safe, coffeemaker and iron/ironing board. Since we were staying for a week I also requested a fridge, which was delivered the same day. We did experience problems with the plumbing once, and maintenance came minutes after I called. The room could use new carpeting and new sink fixtures, the shower had good water pressure. We had no problems with the elevators, even when the hotel was full. Service was very good. The staff (registration desk, card club personnel and cocktail waitresses were very friendly. Whenever I called the front desk the phone was quickly answered. The card club offered items for joining and comps which we applied to the room cost, as well as cash rewards. Room rates were great - $340 for a week and that was for a busy time -- rodeo days. There is a 24 hour McDonald's if you want a quick bite to eat. We did not eat in the restaurant/buffet after reading the trip reports complaining about the food. But there are many restaurants nearby. I recommend Golden Gate, Las Vegas Club and Lanai at the Fremont. If you plan to go shopping or to the Strip it is a short walk to the bus depot. There was plenty of entertainment on Fremont Street.Note - it costs $7 to $8 for a shuttle to or from the airport. It took us an hour to get from the airport to downtown, because the shuttle dropped people off at hotels on the strip first. To take a taxi to the airport was $28 (not including the tip).	
