Jul 19 2006	OK......	My husband and I stayed at the Fitz on July 14th &amp;15th. We have been to vegas many times but never stayed downtown. We normally don't use TA's but we booked our airfare through one and got two nights at the Fitz for mere pennies more. We arrived not expecting much after reading all the reviews on here. Check-in was quick and painless for arriving at 5pm on a Friday. The front desk staff was pleasant. We requested a room on a high floor despite the complaints about the elevators. We got a corner room on the 25th floor. The room was outdated, the bedspreads worn and there was an empty spot above one of the beds where a picure once hung. The bathroom was a nice size with good water pressure. We had an excellent view of the mountains and it was nice to watch the sun come up in the morning. The beds were not very comfortable but after staying out gambling till the wee hours it didn't bother us too much, if we were staying more than two nights it would have really disappointed me. The comments about the elevators were completely true. We waited about ten minutes every time we had to go up to our room. And coming down, we stopped at nearly every floor. Plus, the elevators were hot and because of the long waits, you were often crammed in with a lot of others making for an uncomfortable ride. We used the parking garage and that was a horror as well. The valet takes up the first six floors and maneuvering around is difficult , especially with a bigger car. I'm sure there have been plenty of accidents in there. The pool is small and located next to the parking garage, but it was very clean and uncrowded. Another plus, its open till 11pm, unlike some strip properties. We liked the location, and being downtown, but probably wouldn't stay there again. If you go there not expecting much, you probably won't be disappointed.	
