wn. I am diabetic, bad knee, and have Meniere's (a type of motion sickness). When we called the front desk to request a service elevator (which were working) for my transportation, we were refused. We explained that I had taken a insulin shot and needed to eat within 30 minutes, but were still refused. They offered to send room service but we knew that would take over an hour. I rode the elevator, without recourse, and we just stayed downstairs and avoided the rooms and elevators. As far as we know, no one was offered compensation for the inconvenience. We checked out a day early due to the elevators, and during check out we asked a bell hop if the elevator problems occurred often, and he nodded.	
