Apr 11 2006	We're going back!	I really went back and forth on my rating, between average and above average. I decided on average because when we returned from our 10 day stay at Fitzgeralds last year, I wrote a letter to management complaining about several issues that we had while we were there. THE NEGATIVES:When we checked in, we were told that the room with a king bed that I had reserved several months in advance was not available and that we would have to take two double beds instead. The desk clerk knew we were on our honeymoon, but refused to upgrade us or try to accomodate us regarding this. If we wanted a suite, she informed us it would be an extra $100 per day. We were on the 27th floor and when we arrived there, we found that the soda machine on our floor was broken and the ice machine dispensed so slowly it took almost five minutes to fill a bucket. Therefore, whenever we wanted a beverage, we had to go up or down a floor. We were also very disappointed that there was no refrigerator in our room, which was a major annoyance due to the length of our stay. Also, with several restaurants in the hotel, we were very surprised that they offered no room service. The elevators were very slow while we were there. We waited on average 5 to 10 minutes, sometimes longer, sometimes shorter. We really didn't mind waiting for them unless we were in a hurry. Which wasn't often because we were on vacation! We ate twice in Molly's buffet; one lunch and one breakfast. Compared to other buffets available in Vegas, this one we found to be overpriced and very limited in selection. Disappointing. We also ate at their coffee shop which is attached to the buffet on our last night there. This was most definitely the worst service we received during our stay. We waited almost half an hour just for the waitress to take our order, then were forced to order off of an extremely limited &quot;late night&quot; menu, then waited nearly an hour for our food. Not a great experience. THE POSITIVES:Our room was surprisingly spacious with an absolutely breathtaking view of the mountains. It was also extremely clean. We had housekeeping in every day to clean and they always left us extra towels and linens without us even having to ask. The room had a small safe so we were able to safely store our valuables as well. With the exception of the desk clerk that checked us in, we absolutely loved the staff at Fitzgeralds! Everyone was unfailingly friendly, polite and helpful, from the cocktail waitresses, table dealers, bartenders, cashiers, security, everyone! Plus, since we were there for 10 days, many of them took notice of us and went out of their way to greet us specially and make conversation. We felt very wanted there and it was wonderful. The casino was great! The slots were pretty loose espeically when compared to the strip. Plus, my husband tried his hand at blackjack, which he had never played before. The dealer went out of his way to help him and gave him tips on how to play! We also loved the balcony that was off of the bar on the second level. It overlooks Fremont Street and is a great place to sit and watch the light show and just watch the people. They also had karaoke several times while we were staying there and the host was excellent with a great book. Long rotation though, which is par for the course. So, at the beginning of my review, I mentioned that I wrote a letter to management. Well, it took 8 months but I received a response from the Vice President of Operations last November. He apologized for the inconveniences that we suffered during our honeymoon and offered us a return incentive. We will shortly be returning to Fitzgeralds and have been comped a suite there for a week! Can't wait to come back and post my next review!	
