Mar 29 2006	Great service at The Fitz	My husband and I just returned from a seven night stay at &quot;The Fitz&quot;. Checked in at around 5:15pm Friday 3/17. We were amazed, there was no one in line to check in! We always come to Vegas on the Friday around St Patricks Day and about the same time of day. We have waited in line at other hotels anywhere from 30 to 90 minutes to check in! Asked to be put on an upper floor away from Fremont street, and although the hotel was totally booked (St Patrick's Day &amp; March Madness) request was happily granted. We were given a great room on the 31st floor. We were a bit worried because of some of the comments about the elevators I had read, but our concerns were unfounded. We only had to wait one time during our whole stay and then not more than 3 or 4 minutes. The elevators were very fast.Stayed away from Molly's Buffet until the last night..again, due to the comments I had read. This buffet is not that bad. The selection is small, but everything offered was excellent. We used the discount coupon from the fun book so we didn't pay full price. We both agreed that if we had not gotten a discount we might have felt that it was too expensive for the offerings compared to other downtown buffets.Had a great time at the casino..no big wins, but that's par for us. Great service from cocktail waitresses. Probably better than other downtown casinos.These people crack us up when they complain about rooms. With the turn-over in these hotels, and the way a lot of people treat property, they can and will get a little &quot;worn&quot; between refurbishings.We have stayed at several strip locations over the years and have to say that once you get on the elevator there isn't much difference from one property to the next. As a matter of fact, one of the worst rooms we ever had was in a higher priced popular strip hotel. Our room at The Fitz was clean upon arrival and was maintained during our stay. OK, so one bedspread had been laundered more than the other and was a little faded..hey it was clean!We had a great time at The Fitz and expect to book there again next year for our annual March pilgrimage!	
