Dec 16 2005	Very clean very friendly very well priced	A friend and I stayed at Fitzgerald's Dec 6-10, 2005. I have been reading the reviews and was therefore more 'on the lookout' for issues than I would have been otherwise. In short, it was an excellent stay at a terrific price (we had a coupon from the Fitz that netted out to $ 17.50/night). ROOM: We checked in at noon and had no problems....room was ready and correct. Carpets were clean and relatively new. No peeling wallpaper, no stains, no missing towels. In short it was roomy, but not huge...very clean and neat. The room was made up each day with no issues. EMPLOYEES: All employees from the font desk to the dealers seemed quite friendly...no issues at all. FOOD: We found the 2nd floor buffet (Molly's) to be priced higher than most. It was really a brunch buffet (we went for breakfast). For breakfast only it was too high...for lunch it was OK.WE LIKED: Parking garage is free and clean, no problems. The McDonalds and Krispy Kreme within the hotel are handy. Live music show is fair. We didn't attend the other shows. Unlike some other write-ups we had no problems waiting for elevators...they were prompt.WE'D SUGGEST: In-room coffee pots would be a nice addition, although it was easy to get at McDonalds.Our room didn't have any available wall outlets outside the bathroom for plugging in a computer. OVERALL: Had a great time, an incredible bargain, and the people and hotel provided more than we had expected for the price. We were on the 29th floor and had a terrific view of the mountains and other downtown hotels.	
