stairs. The hotel does have a single outdoor pool and whirpool. Both of these items are very basic and would compare to what you would expect to find in a residental backyard. The casino does have a nice balcony that is accessable from the second floor and looks over fremont street experience. The hotel also has a great location being on the fremont street. I will sum up this lengthy review as the hotel is a great stay and the price is right. We payed about 50 a night including friday and saturday night. Check out the hotel and see for yourself.	
