Aug 10 2005	Fitzgerald's is a Budget Hotel	We stayed at Fitzgerald's from 8/3-8/6/05. The room was clean and practical. The Buffet had a poor selection, the floor was sticky, and the booths needed the cushions to be replaced, you practically fell to the ground when sitting down. The Cafe charged exorbitant prices, i.e., two cups of coffee and one order hash browns was $6. Take the local bus for $2 a person, and you can locate a Denny's on Las Vegas Blvd., and a Carl's, Jr., which is a hamburger joint, however, more economical. There is also a McDonald's in the lobby, however, they never get your order correct, and had poor management. At all costs, avoid the bus tour with Triple J Tours to the Grand Canyon. They advertise a tour of 13 hours, which turns into 16 hours, with no regard to schedule adherence. One hour is devoted to picking up passengers at other hotels. You only get two stops in the Canyon, and they want you to pay $10 to see a film. The complimentary lunch is pizza/lemonade. If you are limited in cash, this is the place to stay, otherwise, try one of the other downtown hotels.	
