orse, the darn thing wouldn't even cool the whole room off. In order to feel any kind of cool breeze, you had to be standing right in front of the unit. Part of the reason it probably never cooled was because the unit was not completely attached to the wall (there was a big gap between the inside wall and outside). We decided that we were going to just deal with it, as we were going to be outside on Freemont St for a good part of the night and we figured that if we left it on while we were gone it would cool off some by the time we got back. That was a big mistake because when we finally got in, it was sooo hot that it was practically unbearable to sleep. Not only was the room temp uncomfortable, but the beds were as well....double beds w/springs poking at your back!!! We somehow made it though the early morning hours and were ready to check out. Overall, everything was gross and dirty-unvacuumed carpet, holes in blankets, bathroom, etc. We did enjoy the dowtown atmosphere; however, we will definitely NOT be staying here again. The customer service, along with old, scruffy rooms does not make it worth the hassle. I paid the same amount of $$$ to stay at the Stratosphere on this trip and it was 10x better.	
