Jan 30 2005	Good Stay at the Fitz	Stayed at the Fitz and downtown for the first time from 8-11 Jan. We were pleased with the hotel staff's courteous service and our room. Location is great, especially during cold or wet weather, because you can walk out the door of one casino and into another without having to walk a great distance, as on the strip. Another reason we chose downtown for this visit was based on hearing that the slots were looser there. We didn't think so, however; in either the Fitz or other casinos we visited. To be fair, it could have just been our luck. We had dinner one night in Molly's Buffet. Service was great and prices were reasonable but, we had a very long wait for entrees. We took a cab on our last day to the strip and had much more fun and playing time on the slots. Even though the casinos there are futher apart, they're more spacious and slots seemed more generous than those downtown. Also, the cocktail waitresses were more abundant and attentive on the strip than at the Fitz and other downtown casinos. If you want to stay downtown, the Fitz is a great place for the price, but we'll stay on the strip again on our next visit.	
