Aug 3 2004	Nice Room Nice People= Great Experience!	Before our trip last weekend to Las Vegas we did some research and saw a number of negative reviews on the Fitz. But, they offered the best deal ($49.00!) for a weekend room and money was an issue (isn't it always?) so we decided to give it a try anyway.Good decision!Frankly, we were expecting an older room that might be in need of remodeling, but even that would have been acceptable. For us, going to Vegas isn't about the room- we're hardly in it anyway. lolWhat we got was a very pleasant surprise!Though we arrived VERY late (2:00AM) due to a terrible accident on the I-15 (we were parked for nearly an hour!), they were able to give us an upgraded, recently remodeled room on the 19th floor with a wonderful view of the strip. It was clean, spacious, quiet and very comfortable.From the moment we arrived to our departure Sunday afternoon, everyone was nice. The food was fine, the casino wasn't too crowded and we won a little money too! (Don't worry, they got it all back!!)We had a great time downtown and happily spent nearly all of Saturday wandering from casino to casino and enjoying the many shops and vendors.Some people have complained about slow elevators and we didn't experience that at all. The longest we waited was perhaps one minute and most of the time it was only a few seconds. Also, and for those of you like me who schlepp their own luggage to and from the car, the parking garage elevators and the guest room elevators are only 50 feet or so apart. I've been in some hotels where it's a half-day hike! For me, it's little things like that that make a big difference. Same thing with the room. Though we were as far from the elevators as possible, because it's not a gigantic hotel, the walk wasn't bad at all.I've never stayed downtown before, but I would book another room at the Fitz without hesitation!Our only complaint, and this is a tiny one, would be the parking garage. It's very small and cramped, but if that's the worst I can think of, I'd say they did a pretty good job!Thank you Fitz for one of the best weekends I've spent in Vegas!	
