Dec 18 2003	Fitzgerald's - Best Deal In Vegas	My wife and I usually stay on the strip, but this last time we decided to stay in &quot;Old Town&quot; for a change, Dec. 6th - 9th 2003. Fitzgeralds was recommended to us, so we decided to stay at Fitzgeralds to check it out.From the time we arrived at Fitzgeralds, we found that the service by all the hotel staff was excellent, from the people in valet parking, the Bell Captain, the front desk clerk and even the Manager On Duty who greeted us.The room and bathroom was clean 100%, and the maid service was very punctual every morning at about 10AM on our floor ... The changed the sheets and cleaned the bathroom everyday.If you want a nice corner room with a nice view, ask for room #1942 on the 19th floor. Nice view of the end of the strip and also of the mountain range.Contrary to what others have written, everytime we summoned the elevator, it was there within a minute or two at the most.Limericks Resturaunt in the hotel was excellent, the food was cooked just as we ordered it , prime rib and their specialty chicken, and was served in a reasonable time without any long wait time even though it was busy.The waitresses that made the rounds we punctual, and they seem come around about every 10-15 minutes without fail. I was impressed, because I was drinking Bud, and every time around, the waitress asked if I would care for another Bud.We are slot players, and it seems that Fitzgerald's is the place for the loose slots in Old Town.Would we go back again - YES, FOR SURE Would we recommend it - YES, FOR SUREPeople complain in their reviews about the bands on Freemont Street. It is unfair, because the ones who write a bad review DO NOT tell you that one stage is in the alley right beside the hotel. OF COURSE YOU WILL HEAR THE MUSIC !!!! The bands only play until 11-12 PM, and most of us are still up at that time. If you are the type that goes to bed at 9 PM, Freemont Street is not for you.For the best deal in &quot;LAS VEGAS&quot; - FITZGERALD's We'll never go back to the strip ..........Al &amp; Mary Springfield, MA	
Nov 30 2003	Very bad experience	Just returned from a 2 week stay in Vegas. I usually stay at the Golden Nugget but this trip I decided to try to save some money (usually my employer is paying but this trip was on me). I had an offer from Fitzgeralds for 3 nights free so I decided to take them up on it. This was the first time I have stayed there. I was in room 1824. Room looked nice at first but soon started finding problems. Noise from Fremont Street Experience and other Bands playing on Fremont Street was unbelievable! I could hardly hear the TV over the noise. Air Conditioner/Heater was very noisy. Toilet wouldn't flush most of the time. Even though I was on the 18th floor, I had a very strong smell of cooking food from the restaurants on the second floor. Parking garage was sort of scary! If I ever did try it again, I would defiantly want a different room! On the plus side, I love their Casino! The great thing about Downtown is you can stay at any of several Hotels and it is a short walk to any of the Fremont Street Casino's. I definitely prefer Downtown to the Strip.	
Nov 26 2003	Used to love the place	My family and I have been part time residents of Vegas for A LONG time! I was married out there and we go out at least 3 times a year. My favorite place to stay and gamble WAS at Fitzgeralds. We were very happy with service, comps and rooms. The last time I was at &quot;The Fitz&quot; Mr O'Lucky was no longer there to rub and I had a the only cocktail waitress that I seen argue with me and poke me with her pen when I tried order two drinks. (one of them for my 78 year old grandfather) What kind of service is that??? Along with the new comp system put into place, I will unfortunatly not be going back when I return to Las Vegas.	
Jul 7 2003	Good place!	I think your reaction to this place will depend on what you pay. It can be insanely cheap here. Fitzgerald's is a giant high rise hotel on Fremont St. in a wonderfully fun location that's a little more realistic that the Strip. There are no super-fancy stores here but the street is covered and pedestrian only with lots of other kind of retro high rise hotel and casinos. I found it very refreshing as an alternative to the major crowds and needless expensive of the Strip. There's a light show every night.The hotel is clean and the rooms are what you'd expect from a 3 star hotel. You may wait a bit to check in but nothing like the monster lines at the places on the Strip. You may be a bit aggravated by the elevator wait. Beyond that, I was pretty happy and would certainly stay again (and I have).	
Jun 30 2003	Where it's at in downtown	My husband and I go to Vegas every year. We stay on the strip for a few days and then down town for a couple more. We just love the Fitzgerald's. The location is great. The light show is there and Limerick's Steakhouse is a must try if you stay at Fitzgerald's. AWESOME! The rooms are tidy and spacious and the staff is pleasant. Best of all it's economical.	
